This is the best Suki I‚Äôve ever tried, and I‚Äôm amazed at how they manage to maintain the quality and taste every single time I visit. How is that even possible? Suki is a simple dish that you can sometimes make at home, but here, they make every element absolutely perfect. The pork is tender and well-seasoned, and the veggies are the real highlight. They fry the vegetables while keeping them incredibly crispy and fresh. As for the Suki sauce, it‚Äôs just right‚Äînot too spicy and not too mild. During peak hours, you might have to wait a bit.
